      "content": "If you are certain there's no damage or logging failure, consider the possibility of phantom inventory resulting from system setup errors. Sometimes, mismatched bin locations or utilizing legacy SKUs with slightly different descriptions can cause the system to count inventory that isn't physically present in its expected location. Additionally, internal transfers between different staging areas might be recorded partially in the system, leading to a discrepancy before the final location is updated. Reviewing your Warehouse Management System (WMS) transfer documentation could reveal these \"ghost\" inventory issues.",
